  "number": "3.5.5.70",
  "title": "",
  "body": "   Town A and Town B are miles apart. A boat traveled from Town A to Town B, and then back to Town A. Since the river flows from Town B to Town A, the boat s speed was miles per hour faster when it traveled from Town B to Town A. The whole trip took hours. Answer the following questions:  The boat traveled from Town A to Town B at the speed of miles per hour.  The boat traveled from Town B back to Town A at the speed of miles per hour.             Assume that the boat traveled from Town A to Town B at miles per hour.  Then, it traveled from Town B back to Town A at miles per hour.  Using the formula , we know the boat traveled from Town A to Town B in hours; and it traveled back from Town B to Town A in hours.  It s given that the whole trip took hours, so we can write an equation and solve it:   When numbers are big, we use the quadratic formula to solve the quadratic equation:   In this situation, is not a valid solution, since speed cannot be negative, is the only solution. The boat traveled from Town A to Town B at the speed of miles per hour.  The boat traveled from Town B back to Town A at the speed of miles per hour.       "
